title: Grateful Dead Live at Boston Garden on 1980-05-12
lineage: MAC > Re-shelled > Nakamichi DR-8 > Edirol FA-66 > Wavelab 2448 > R8Brain > CD-Wave > TLH > FLAC 16; Transfer by Andrew F.
description:
Set 1

Jack Straw-> Alabama Getaway-> El Paso, Althea, Lazy Lightning-> Supplication-> Far From Me, Minglewood Blues, China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider

Set 2

Feel Like A Stranger, Ship of Fools-> Estimated Prophet-> He's Gone-> Drums-> Saint Of Circumstance-> Wharf Rat-> Sugar Magnolia, E: U.S. Blues

reviews.review_text: Love it, Jerry, Bobby Orr and John Havlicek I don't know about whole star rating system, and some folks seem to get riled up about it, but why not start this one off with five.  Five because it sounds great, (especially for Boston Garden) and five because this was one of the very first tapes I had, and five becuase the jack straw should be on some "best of" lists, and the alabama is paced so frenetically.   I also love the china-rider jam, jerry's voice on the north-bound train verse, and so on.   Thanks!
